compiler, Don't known / other

### Is this a regression?

No

### Description

The following type defines an optional property with a required child object:

```typescript
interface Demo {
  optionalProp?: {
    requiredProp: {
      value: string;
    };
  };
}
```

When accessing the `value` property we need to use optional chaining to make sure that `optionalProp` is not undefined. The following statement works as expected in the component class (`test` is of type `Demo`):

```typescript
// app.component.ts
console.log(this.test.optionalProp?.requiredProp.value);
```

Accessing the value in the HTML template of the component doesn't work. 

```html
<p>{{ test.optionalProp?.requiredProp.value }}</p>
```

It shows an error that `requiredProp` is possibly undefined.

<img width="865" alt="Bildschirmfoto 2022-07-06 um 14 51 50" src="https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/16229645/177554351-29a72a6a-9e99-4043-a112-826c679244b9.png">

The error is shown by the Angular Language Service and when building the app. Adding "?" after `requiredProp` works but should not be required.

```
<p>{{ test.optionalProp?.requiredProp?.value }}</p>
```

